name: Dropdown
description: Dropdown UI element that expands once clicked

name: Dynamic component
description: A button that triggers loading of external diagram on top of it

name: Frame-by-frame diagram
description:
Lets you design simple animated diagram that shows elements frame by frame.
To make it work you need to tag your items with "frame-1", "frame-2", "frame-3" and so on for every frame

name: Popup
description: A popup with open and closing animations

name: Prototype
description: Helps designing a basic app prototype with multiple app pages. Each page has an "Open Page" event that, once triggered, displays that page on top.

name: Sankey diagram
description:
This template converts your diagram code below into an interactive Sankey diagram.
To define a connection in your diagram between the two nodes "A" and "B" type it like this "A [150] B".
Every connection should be defined in a separate line.

name: Slider
description: Allows users to drag slider in view mode and change its value. This slider can be used as an input to some Script function
